                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Tarjumah-i Qutb-Shahi.</title>
                     <note>According to Reade missing from bod 140, but it is there now, Oct 2009. Incomplete at end. F1a: Note in Arabic making the book waqf on the same conditions as 'rest of the books', beside a faint impression of an oval seal. A translation of the Arabic Arba'in Hadith of Baha' al-Din 'Amili, by Muhammad b. 'Ali 'Amili, known as Ibn Khatun, made for Sultan Muhammad Qutb Shah. Headings and punctuation in red. For scribe's name see f.9a.</note>
                     <incipit>Ay az tu hadith-i ma'rifat-ra tabyin</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>None found for the translation. For the Arabic original see Brockelmann.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
